# Creating Promises

You can create a promise using the `Promise` constructor:

```javascript
const myPromise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  // async operation
  if (/* success */) {
    resolve(value);
  } else {
    reject(error);
  }
});
```

- `resolve` – function to call when the operation succeeds, passing the result.
- `reject` – function to call when it fails, passing an error.

This is often used to **promisify** callback-based functions.

slides.codeSnippet:
function wait(ms) {
  return new Promise(resolve => {
    setTimeout(resolve, ms);
  });
}

wait(2000).then(() => console.log('2 seconds later'));

